<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <title>Free Webhooks: Cloud, Self-Hosted or Playground | Hook0</title>
    <%
    locals.pageTitle = 'Free Webhooks: Cloud, Self-Hosted or Playground | Hook0';
    locals.pageDescription = 'Three genuinely free ways to use Hook0: test webhooks in your browser with no account, self-host the open-source server (SSPL-1.0) unlimited, or a free cloud tier with no credit card.';
    locals.pageCanonical = '/webhook-free';
    locals.pageFAQSchema = {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "FAQPage",
      "mainEntity": [
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Is Hook0 really free?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Yes, in three honest ways. play.hook0.com is a free tool to test and inspect webhooks in your browser, no account needed. The open-source server is free forever to self-host with no volume cap imposed by Hook0 (SSPL-1.0). And Hook0 Cloud has a free Developer tier: 100 events/day, no credit card, no feature gating. No bait-and-switch."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Is there a free open-source webhook server?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Yes. Hook0 is a free, open-source webhook server under SSPL-1.0, published on GitHub and GitLab. It ships with Docker Compose and Kubernetes manifests and runs on PostgreSQL. Self-hosting is free with no license cost and no volume cap from Hook0. It is the same codebase as the cloud, with the same features."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What are the free tier limits on Hook0 Cloud?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "The free Developer tier includes 1 developer, 1 application, 10 event types, 10 subscriptions, up to 100 events/day, and 7 days of data retention. All delivery features are included: HMAC signing, retries, delivery logs and the subscriber portal. No credit card is required and the tier is free forever for side-projects."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Can I test a webhook for free without an account?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Yes. play.hook0.com gives you a public URL to receive, inspect and replay webhook payloads directly in your browser. There is nothing to install and no signup. It is free and itself open-source."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Is self-hosting Hook0 free?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Yes. There is no license cost and no volume cap imposed by Hook0 when you self-host. You provide the infrastructure (Docker or Kubernetes plus PostgreSQL) and get community support on Discord. Managed scaling, an uptime SLA and managed updates are the things you take on yourself when self-hosting."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What is the difference between play.hook0.com and Hook0 Cloud?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "play.hook0.com is a free tool to receive, inspect and debug webhooks that other services send you. Hook0 Cloud is the infrastructure to send signed webhooks to your own users in production, with retries, a dead letter queue and a subscriber portal. Use Play to debug, use Cloud or self-hosted to ship."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Does the free cloud tier expire or require a credit card?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "No. The free Developer tier has no time limit and requires no credit card. It is free forever for side-projects."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What happens when I exceed the free cloud tier?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Events beyond 100/day on the free tier are blocked until the next day. To send more, you upgrade to a paid plan (Startup at €59/mo excl. VAT, or Pro). Paid plans only unlock higher volume and support; no feature is locked behind them. If you want no volume cap at all, self-host the open-source server for free."
          }
        }
      ]
    };
    %>
    <%- include('./includes/_head.ejs') %>
</head>
<body>
<%- include('./includes/_header.ejs') %>

<!-- Hero Section -->
<section class="relative gradient-hero overflow-hidden py-20 sm:py-28">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 grid-pattern opacity-50"></div>
    <div class="blur-circle blur-circle--indigo w-96 h-96 -top-48 -left-48"></div>
    <div class="blur-circle blur-circle--green w-80 h-80 top-1/2 -right-40"></div>

    <div class="relative z-10 max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
        <span class="section__eyebrow">Free Webhooks</span>
        <h1 class="mt-4 text-display-xl text-white">
            Free webhooks, three honest ways
            <span class="block text-gradient-green">Test one now, or run the server for free</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="mt-6 text-body-lg text-gray-400 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
            Three things at Hook0 are genuinely free, with no hidden paywall. <strong class="text-gray-200">play.hook0.com</strong> inspects and tests any webhook, no account. The <strong class="text-gray-200">open-source server</strong> (SSPL-1.0) self-hosts unlimited on your own infra. And <strong class="text-gray-200">Hook0 Cloud</strong> has a free tier: 100 events/day, no credit card, no feature gating. Pick what you actually need.
        </p>

        <div class="mt-10 flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
            <a href="https://play.hook0.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn btn--primary btn--lg group" onclick="trackEvent('CTA', 'Click', 'webhook-free-hero-play')">
                Test a webhook now
                <svg class="w-5 h-5 ml-2 group-hover:translate-x-1 transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 7l5 5m0 0l-5 5m5-5H6"></path>
                </svg>
            </a>
            <a href="https://documentation.hook0.com/self-hosting/docker-compose" class="btn btn--secondary btn--lg" onclick="trackEvent('CTA', 'Click', 'webhook-free-hero-selfhost')">
                Self-host the server free
            </a>
        </div>
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-gray-500">No account to test · Unlimited self-host · Free cloud tier, no credit card</p>

        <figure class="mt-14 max-w-3xl mx-auto animate-on-scroll">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 720 110" role="img" aria-labelledby="flow-title flow-desc" class="w-full h-auto" style="max-width:720px;">
            <title id="flow-title">How Hook0 delivers a webhook</title>
            <desc id="flow-desc">An event is signed with HMAC, delivered, automatically retried after a 503 error, then accepted with a 200 response.</desc>
            <defs>
              <style>
                .h0n{fill:#14141a;}
                .h0lbl{font-family:ui-monospace,'SFMono-Regular',Menlo,monospace;font-size:13px;fill:#e5e7eb;}
                .h0sub{font-family:ui-monospace,'SFMono-Regular',Menlo,monospace;font-size:10px;fill:#9ca3af;}
                .h0dash{stroke:#818cf8;stroke-width:2.5;stroke-dasharray:5 9;animation:h0flow 1.1s linear infinite;}
                @keyframes h0flow{to{stroke-dashoffset:-14;}}
              </style>
            </defs>
            <!-- baseline + animated event flow (visible in the gaps between stages) -->
            <line x1="104" y1="66" x2="704" y2="66" stroke="rgba(255,255,255,.14)" stroke-width="2.5"/>
            <line x1="104" y1="66" x2="704" y2="66" class="h0dash"/>
            <!-- stages -->
            <g>
              <rect class="h0n" x="8" y="44" width="96" height="44" rx="8" stroke="rgba(255,255,255,.22)"/>
              <text class="h0lbl" x="56" y="71" text-anchor="middle">event</text>
            </g>
            <g>
              <rect class="h0n" x="128" y="44" width="96" height="44" rx="8" stroke="rgba(255,255,255,.22)"/>
              <text class="h0lbl" x="176" y="64" text-anchor="middle">sign</text>
              <text class="h0sub" x="176" y="79" text-anchor="middle">HMAC</text>
            </g>
            <g>
              <rect class="h0n" x="248" y="44" width="96" height="44" rx="8" stroke="rgba(255,255,255,.22)"/>
              <text class="h0lbl" x="296" y="71" text-anchor="middle">deliver</text>
            </g>
            <g>
              <rect class="h0n" x="368" y="44" width="96" height="44" rx="8" stroke="#fe884e"/>
              <text class="h0lbl" x="416" y="71" text-anchor="middle" fill="#fdba74">503</text>
            </g>
            <g>
              <rect class="h0n" x="488" y="44" width="96" height="44" rx="8" stroke="#fe884e"/>
              <text class="h0lbl" x="536" y="71" text-anchor="middle" fill="#fdba74">retry</text>
            </g>
            <g>
              <rect class="h0n" x="608" y="44" width="96" height="44" rx="8" stroke="#818cf8"/>
              <text class="h0lbl" x="656" y="71" text-anchor="middle" fill="#c7d2fe">200 ✓</text>
            </g>
          </svg>
          <figcaption class="mt-4 text-center text-sm text-gray-500">Every event is signed (HMAC), delivered, retried automatically on failure, then logged, whether on the cloud or self-hosted.</figcaption>
        </figure>
    </div>
</section>

<%- include('./includes/_social-proof-bar.ejs') %>

